EXT. SURVEYOR CRATER, APOLLO 12 SITE - LUNAR DAY

The prime rover crests a low ridge, camera boom high, three suits aboard. Below: the Apollo 12 descent stage, gold foil still bright, experiment packages ranked where men left them in 1969.

LINDQVIST:
(reading from a cue card clipped to his cuff)
"We arrive as guests of history, to relieve it of its oldest burden—"

He stops reading.

The flag is missing. A socket hole stands in the gray. Around it, the bootprints are recent, and they aren't theirs. Wheel tracks lead in and out of the site.

BRANDT:
Harmony, Site One. The artifact is... not present.

INT. FRONTIER MISSION CONTROL - CONTINUOUS

Rows of faces, nobody moving. On the main screen, the empty socket hole, full screen.

FLIGHT DIRECTOR:
Say again, Harmony One?

BRANDT (V.O.):
The flag is gone. The site is otherwise intact. We observe recent surface activity. Bootprints. Vehicle tracks.

INT. UNITY DAY PAVILION, WASHINGTON - CONTINUOUS

A daytime stage dressed in harmony blue, schoolchildren holding little Harmony Banners. Marwani mid-remarks at a podium, teleprompter rolling. Behind him, the giant screen cuts from the live feed to a graphic reading PLEASE STAND BY: UNITY DAY.

An AIDE climbs the stage steps and whispers. Marwani keeps smiling at the children while he listens.

INT. JOSS'S TRUCK - CONTINUOUS

The phone on the dash shows a jittery re-stream of the raw feed, chat scrolling too fast to read.

JOSS:
They can't cut the raw loop. It relays through nine countries.

DANNY:
Where are the flags, Joss?

Joss looks at the ham rig. Says nothing. Two clicks come out of it, soft. Then two more.

EXT. FRA MAURO, APOLLO 14 SITE - LATER

The rover parked. Three suits standing at another socket hole, another ring of prints, the same wheel tracks arriving and leaving.

Lindqvist holds his cue card, doesn't read it.

ON A STREAMER'S FEED (INSET)

A man in a gaming chair, veins out.

STREAMER:
There were NEVER any flags! Fifty years of soundstage! They're on the Moon looking for PROPS, people! WAKE UP!

INT. ROY'S DINER - CONTINUOUS

On the TV, the socket hole again. Buck turns his cup a quarter turn.

BUCK:
Somebody took 'em.

EARLENE:
Took 'em where, Buck? It's the Moon.

Buck drinks his coffee. A smile starts on his face, slow.

EXT. FRA MAURO - CONTINUOUS

Brandt stands over the wheel tracks. Follows them with his visor to where they run off northwest, dead straight, out of sight.

He switches to the private crew loop. Click.

SHEN:
(on the private loop)
Commander. The possibility must be raised. If the artifacts were never — if the landings themselves were—

BRANDT:
Don't.

Silence on the loop. Shen looks at the bootprints. Fifty years of undisturbed prints ring the socket, the new ones laid over them, crisp-edged and fresh.

BRANDT:
Mount up. Last site on the program.

LINDQVIST:
Tranquility Base.

Brandt takes one more look northwest along the wheel tracks, dead straight, toward Tranquility.

BRANDT:
Whoever they are, they're not hiding their driving.

CUT TO:
